summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Fifty ($50.00) out of the water fund of the City of Seattle, in settlement of the claim of Edith L. Dearborn for damages to north thirty (30) feet of Lot three (3), Block seven (7), East Park Addition to the City of Seattle, caused by the breaking of a watermain in Bellevue Place, on the 13th day of February 1916, in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
